<Layout title="Keychain" maturity="budding">
<p>
  <a href="https://www.funtoo.org/Funtoo:Keychain">Keychain</a>
  can be used to add <a href="ssh-key.html">SSH keys</a> to the ssh-agent.
</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>
<p>Keychain does not come pre-installed on most systems, so first install Keychain:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-sh">sudo apt install keychain</code></pre>

<h2>Add an SSH key to Keychain</h2>
<p>To add a private SSH key to Keychain, execute:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-sh">keychain ~/.ssh/id_ed25519</code></pre>
<p>
  This process can be automated by having this command in the <a href="bash.html">Bash</a> or
  <a href="zsh.html">Zsh</a> configuration file.
</p>
<p>
  Keychain has the benefit of starting ssh-agent if it has not already been started,
  and can be used to add GPG keys.
</p>

<h2 id="list-loaded-ssh-keys">List loaded SSH keys</h2>
<p>Use the <code>-l</code> flag to list all the loaded SSH keys:</code>
<pre><code class="lang-sh">keychain -l</code></pre>
</Layout>